{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-situations-page-tsx","path":"/en/situations/leisure-time/staying-park","result":{"data":{"situation":{"title":"Staying in the park","meta_description":"Staying in the park is allowed. ","content":{"processed":"<h2>Rules and recommendations</h2>\n<p>Staying in the park is <strong>allowed</strong>. Staying in the fresh air is recommended, but it should not be exaggerated - you should stay in the park with one other person maximum. The clustering of more than two people is <strong>prohibited</strong>. People living in the same household are the exception.</p>\n<p>Avoid other people and keep a <strong>two-meters distance</strong>. If you cannot avoid other people, <strong>wear a face mask</strong>. We recommend wearing a face mask throughout the whole stay in the park. It is <strong>forbidden</strong> to consume alcohol there. <strong>Wash your hands</strong> thoroughly when you return home.</p>\n<p>And of course, it is <strong>forbidden</strong> to visit the park during the curfew (9 PM - 4.59 AM). If you are a lover of midnight walk, you are unfortunately out of luck.</p>\n"},"path":{"alias":"/situations/leisure-time/staying-park"},"valid_from":"2020-11-04T00:00:00+01:00","links":[],"relationships":{"region":[{"name":"All regions of Czechia"}],"icon":{"code":"nature_people"},"situation_type":{"name":"Leisure time","path":{"alias":"/situations/leisure-time"},"relationships":{"icon":{"code":"deck"}}},"measures":[],"related_situations":[{"title":"Measures on free movement","path":{"alias":"/situations/free-movement-people/measures-free-movement","langcode":"en"}}]},"questions_answers":[{"question":"Can I have a picnic in the park? ","value":"Yes, but it must comply with the current rules on the freedom of movement. (Only two people with the exception for people from one household and ban of alcohol consumption.)\r\n"},{"question":"Can I drink alcohol in the park with my friends? ","value":"No. It is prohibited to consume a